\p \v 28 All this [oeb:happened to|:came upon] [oeb:|:the ]King Nebuchadnezzar: \v 29 At the end of twelve months he was walking in the royal palace of Babylon. \v 30 The king [oeb:|:spoke and] said, “Is not this great Babylon which I have built for a residence, by the might of my power and for the glory of my majesty?” \v 31 While the word was in the king’s mouth, a voice came down from heaven: “[oeb:|:O ]King Nebuchadnezzar, to [oeb:you|:thee] it is spoken: The kingdom [oeb:has|:hath] passed away from [oeb:you|:thee], \v 32 and [oeb:you will|:thou shalt] be driven from [oeb:people|:men], and [oeb:your home|:thy dwelling] [oeb:will|:shall] be with the [oeb:animals|:beasts] of the field; [oeb:you will|:thou shalt] be made to eat grass as oxen; and seven times [oeb:will|:shall] pass over [oeb:you|:thee], until [oeb:you know|:thou knowest] that the Most High [oeb:rules|:ruleth] in [oeb:human|:the] kingdom[oeb:s|:] [oeb:|:of men ]and give[oeb:s|:][oeb:|:th] [oeb:them|:it] to whom he will.” \v 33 The same hour the word was fulfilled upon Nebuchadnezzar; and he was driven from [oeb:people|:men], and ate grass like oxen, and his body was wet with the dew of heaven, until his hair had grown like eagles’ feathers and his nails like birds’ claws. 

\p \v 34 [oeb:A|:And a]t the end of the [oeb:appointed time |:days ]I, Nebuchadnezzar, lifted up my eyes to heaven, and my reason returned to me, and I blessed the Most High, and praised and honored him who live[oeb:s|:][oeb:|:th] forever; for his dominion is an everlasting dominion and his kingdom [oeb:lasts|:from] generation to generation; \v 25 and all the inhabitants of the earth are considered as nothing; and he doe[oeb:s|:th] according to his will in the army of heaven, and among the inhabitants of the earth; and n[oeb:o oone can stay his hand, or say to him. What |:][oeb:are you doing|:doest thou]? \v 36 At that same time my reason returned to me, and for the sake of my royal honor, my majesty and my kingly appearance were restored to me. Then my counsellors and my nobles sought eagerly for me; and I was established in my kingdom, and still greater power was added to me. \v 37 Now I, Nebuchadnezzar, praise and extol and honor the King of heaven, for all his works are truth, and his ways justice; and those who walk in pride he is able to [oeb:humble|:abase].

